The paper deals with algorithms for maintaining shortest paths and betweenness centrality in a directed graph, which are fundamental problems in computer science. The use of amortized analysis and the focus on decremental updates suggest that the paper belongs to the data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. The application of the algorithm to large complex networks and the mention of the number of edges in the graph suggest that the paper may also belong to the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The use of graphs and the mention of edge weights suggest that the paper may belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Finally, the mention of betweenness centrality and the analysis of large complex networks suggest that the paper may also belong to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
